            "new_string": "Overhead model per syscall (three components):\n- Notification cost: USER_NOTIF ~10.8us, RET_TRAP ~3.6us (measured), rewrite ~0.04us (est)\n- Cross-process copy: `process_vm_readv/writev` ~1-2us (eliminated in Tier 1/2)\n- LKL + host I/O: varies by syscall, unchanged across tiers\n\n### Tier 1 (RET_TRAP) -- measured 2026-03-23\n\nMeasured on node1 (x86_64), release build, `tests/guest/trap-bench`\n(static asm binary, no libc/TLS -- avoids arch_prctl blocker).\ngetpid-only loop, 10000 iterations, median of 3 runs.\n\n| Mode | getpid (10K) | per-call | vs native |\n|------|-------------|---------|-----------|\n| native | 2.98ms | 0.30us | 1.0x |\n| seccomp (USER_NOTIF) | 108ms | 10.8us | 36x |\n| trap (RET_TRAP) | 36ms | 3.6us | 12x |\n\nTrap mode is 3.0x faster than seccomp for the pure notification\nround-trip. The 3.6us/call overhead is:\n- Signal delivery + ucontext save/restore: ~1-2us on x86_64.\n- kbox dispatch: syscall number lookup, fd table check, LKL dispatch\n  (getpid returns hardcoded PID 1), result writeback: ~1.5us.\n- The seccomp notification floor (10.8us) includes kernel-side\n  seccomp_do_user_notification + poll + recv + send + response copy,\n  all eliminated by trap mode.\n\n### Updated projections (Tier 1 measured, Tier 2 estimated)\n\n| Syscall | seccomp (lazy shadow) | Tier 1 (trap, est) | Tier 2 (rewrite, est) | native |\n|---------|----------------------|--------------------|-----------------------|--------|\n| stat | 18.0us | ~10us | ~7us | 2.2us |\n| open+close | 25.5us | ~11us | ~4us | 2.9us |\n| lseek+read | 24.0us | ~10us | ~2.5us | 1.0us |\n| write | 24.5us | ~17us | ~14us | 1.1us |\n| getpid | 10.8us | **3.6us** | ~0.04us | 0.3us |\n\nTier 1 projections use the measured 3.6us signal cost. For two-syscall\nworkloads (open+close, lseek+read), double the signal cost (~7.2us).\nLKL + host I/O cost unchanged. Cross-process copy eliminated (in-process\nmemcpy). open+close benefits from both lazy shadow AND elimin